    "origin": "native",
    "serialization": "borsh",
    "description": "Liquidation-aware AMM lending protocol: a single program combining a CPMM AMM with collateralized lending, where liquidation executes inside swap. Supports SPL Token and Token 2022. Instruction discriminators are single-byte Borsh enum variant indexes (NOT Anchor 8-byte sighashes); error codes are the raw ProgramError::Custom index (0-based, NOT Anchor's 6000-based)."
  },
  "instructions": [
    {
      "name": "initializePool",
      "discriminator": [
        0
      ],
      "docs": [
        "Initialize a new (mintA, mintB) pool. Mints must be sorted (mintA < mintB) so the pool PDA is canonical.",
        "Creates the two vaults and the LP mint; validates that neither mint carries a dangerous Token-2022 extension.",
        "Pools are IMMUTABLE and AUTHORITY-LESS: all economics (fees, liq ratio, LTV, interest curve) are fixed program constants and the pool authority is set to the zero pubkey. Takes no arguments; the creator gains no rights."
      ],
