      "discriminator": [
        7
      ],
      "docs": [
        "Swap with mandatory in-flight liquidation (DESIGN.md §7).",
        "The caller supplies every band + all of its open loans whose liquidation the price move might trigger. The program iteratively reprices, liquidates the next crossed loan, and repeats, then quotes the swap on the post-liquidation reserves and commits only if min_out and the executable-reserve cap are satisfied.",
        "Beyond the 9 fixed accounts below, the instruction takes a variable tail: for each entry i in bandLoanCounts, one writable Band PDA followed by bandLoanCounts[i] writable Loan accounts (all of that band's open loans, sorted strictly ascending by pubkey)."
      ],
